modules.name: AWS.Comprehend
modules.comments: Amazon Comprehend is an AWS service for gaining insight into the content of documents. Use these actions to determine the topics contained in your documents, the topics they discuss, the predominant sentiment expressed in them, the predominant language used, and more.

declarations.comments: Determines the dominant language of the input text for a batch of documents. For a list of languages that Amazon Comprehend can detect, see Amazon Comprehend Supported Languages.
declarations.title: batchDetectDominantLanguage

declarations.comments: Inspects the text of a batch of documents and returns information about them. For more information about entities, see how-entities
declarations.title: batchDetectEntities

declarations.comments: Detects the key noun phrases found in a batch of documents.
declarations.title: batchDetectKeyPhrases

declarations.comments: Inspects a batch of documents and returns an inference of the prevailing sentiment, POSITIVE, NEUTRAL, MIXED, or NEGATIVE, in each one.
declarations.title: batchDetectSentiment

declarations.comments: Gets the properties associated with a topic detection job. Use this operation to get the status of a detection job.
declarations.title: describeTopicsDetectionJob

declarations.comments: Determines the dominant language of the input text. For a list of languages that Amazon Comprehend can detect, see Amazon Comprehend Supported Languages.
declarations.title: detectDominantLanguage

declarations.comments: Inspects text for entities, and returns information about them. For more information, about entities, see how-entities.
declarations.title: detectEntities

declarations.comments: Detects the key noun phrases found in the text.
declarations.title: detectKeyPhrases

declarations.comments: Inspects text and returns an inference of the prevailing sentiment (POSITIVE, NEUTRAL, MIXED, or NEGATIVE).
declarations.title: detectSentiment

declarations.comments: Gets a list of the topic detection jobs that you have submitted.
declarations.title: listTopicsDetectionJobs

declarations.comments: Starts an asynchronous topic detection job. Use the DescribeTopicDetectionJob operation to track the status of a job.
declarations.title: startTopicsDetectionJob

declarations.comments: The result of calling the operation. The operation returns one object for each document that is successfully processed by the operation.
declarations.title: BatchDetectDominantLanguageItemResult

declarations.comments: The result of calling the operation. The operation returns one object for each document that is successfully processed by the operation.
declarations.title: BatchDetectEntitiesItemResult

declarations.comments: The result of calling the operation. The operation returns one object for each document that is successfully processed by the operation.
declarations.title: BatchDetectKeyPhrasesItemResult

declarations.comments: The result of calling the operation. The operation returns one object for each document that is successfully processed by the operation.
declarations.title: BatchDetectSentimentItemResult

declarations.comments: Describes an error that occurred while processing a document in a batch. The operation returns on BatchItemError object for each document that contained an error.
declarations.title: BatchItemError

declarations.comments: The number of documents in the request exceeds the limit of 25. Try your request again with fewer documents.
declarations.title: BatchSizeLimitExceededException

declarations.comments: Returns the code for the dominant language in the input text and the level of confidence that Amazon Comprehend has in the accuracy of the detection.
declarations.title: DominantLanguage

declarations.comments: Provides information about an entity.
declarations.title: Entity

declarations.comments: The input properties for a topic detection job.
declarations.title: InputDataConfig

declarations.comments: An internal server error occurred. Retry your request.
declarations.title: InternalServerException

declarations.comments: The filter specified for the ListTopicDetectionJobs operation is invalid. Specify a different filter.
declarations.title: InvalidFilterException

declarations.comments: The request is invalid.
declarations.title: InvalidRequestException

declarations.comments: The specified job was not found. Check the job ID and try again.
declarations.title: JobNotFoundException

declarations.comments: Describes a key noun phrase.
declarations.title: KeyPhrase

declarations.comments: Provides configuration parameters for the output of topic detection jobs.
declarations.title: OutputDataConfig

declarations.comments: Describes the level of confidence that Amazon Comprehend has in the accuracy of its detection of sentiments.
declarations.title: SentimentScore

declarations.comments: The size of the input text exceeds the limit. Use a smaller document.
declarations.title: TextSizeLimitExceededException

declarations.comments: The number of requests exceeds the limit. Resubmit your request later.
declarations.title: TooManyRequestsException

declarations.comments: Provides information for filtering topic detection jobs. For more information, see .
declarations.title: TopicsDetectionJobFilter

declarations.comments: Provides information about a topic detection job.
declarations.title: TopicsDetectionJobProperties

declarations.comments: Amazon Comprehend can't process the language of the input text. For all APIs except DetectDominantLanguage, Amazon Comprehend accepts only English or Spanish text. For the DetectDominantLanguage API, Amazon Comprehend detects 100 languages. For a list of languages, see how-languages
declarations.title: UnsupportedLanguageException
